Dead Hidden Services

Do not simply remove services that appear to be offline from the above list! Services can go down temporarily
column1659:
so we keep track of when they do and maintain a list of dead hidden services.

  • In addition to an onion simply being gone (Tor cannot resolve the onion)
column1660:
sites that display 404 (and use a known onion/URL based hosting service) are the only other thing that is considered truly DOWN. Presumably the account is gone.
  1. If a service has been down for a while
column1661:
tag it with ' - DOWN YYYY-MM-DD' (your guess as to when it went down).
  • If a tagged service on the above list of live hidden services has come back up
column1662:
remove the DOWN tag.
  • If a tagged service is still down after a month
column1663:
please move it (along with the DOWN tag) to the list of dead hidden services.
  • The general idea of the remaining four service states below is that
column1664: if the Hidden Service Descriptor is available
column1665: and something is responding behind it... the service is considered up
column1666: and we track that fact on the Main Page. If any of these subsequently go offline
column1667:
append the DOWN tag and handle as above.
  1. Hello world's / statements
column1670:
etc (while boring)... are listed as usual.
  • Broken services are those that display 404 (and do not use a known hosting service)
column1671: PHP or other errors (or they fail silently)... any of which prevent the use of the service as intended. They also include blank pages
column1672:
empty dirs and neglected status notes. Presumably the operator is in limbo. Broken services are tagged with ' (reason) - Broken YYYY-MM-DD' (your guess as to when it went broken)
  • Services that automatically redirect to another service (such as by HTTP protocol or script)
column1673:
have their redirection destinations noted in their descriptions. These are tagged with ' - Redir YYYY-MM-DD' (your guess as to when it went redir)
  • Sites that are formally closed via announcement are tagged with ' - Closed YYYY-MM-DD' (your guess as to when it went closed.
    • Is Online that HiddenService? This service is very useful in determining whether onions are up or not. It also gives a reason why they are down.

    Sites on this list that have no chance of coming back (LE takedowns
column1674: dead for some time) should be archived to page dead services just in case they should ever be needed.
